Durban - Police are looking for two missing sisters after a father claimed he could not find them. Durban Central police said they are looking for missing sisters Tasmiya and Aisha Hassim. “The father claims he cannot find Tasmiya and Aisha at the addresses submitted by the mother in terms of the high court order to visit the children. The mother left the country for Dubai,” police said. According to the missing persons report, anyone with information on the girls’ whereabouts can contact Constable ES Tshabalala at 084 8917287 or Durban Central  police on 031 325 4225, 031 325 4690. The report said the sisters went missing on February 14, 2018. Aisha, who is under the age of 10, has brown hair, brown eyes, is 1m tall, weighs 25kg and is of average build. Tasmiya is between the ages of 10 and 18. She also has brown hair and brown eyes. She is 1.2m tall, weighs 40kg and is also of average build. Daily News